What Havard's History books won't tell you.

Did you know that...
Aaron Burr was not the romantic rebel of modern popular fiction, but a spy for theand the Swiss opponents of the American Revolution?
The Secretary of the Treasury of the United States in 1801-1813 was a swiss nobleman sent here to direct a foreign takeover of the U.S. Financial system?

More on the back cover.

More recent articles by Anton Chaitkin at www.larouchepub.com and www.larouchepac.com


